  <p> 
  <h2>The Power of Small Habits in Creating Lasting Change<h2>
   <p>In today’s fast-paced world, we’re often looking for quick fixes and instant results, but real, lasting<br>
   change usually comes from small, consistent actions. Whether it’s improving your health, mastering a<br>
   new skill, or building stronger relationships, success doesn’t happen overnight. It’s the tiny, everyday<br>
   habits that compound over time to create remarkable transformations.<br></p>
   <p>One of the key reasons small habits work so well is because they’re easier to maintain. Rather than<br>
   overhauling your entire routine or setting ambitious (and often overwhelming) goals, starting with a<br>
   small, manageable habit makes it more likely you’ll stick with it. This gradual approach reduces<br>
   resistance and gives you the momentum needed to stay on track.<br></p>
